uniGLMM

COMMON UNIVARIATE RANDOM INTERCEPT

TAKE-HOME MESSAGE: PARALLELIZATION + PARAMETER_VECTOR() + dnorm() + MODELING THE log(sd) WORKS NICELY!

J <- 250
cs <- 10
beta.mcie <- c(beta1=0.85, beta2=1.25)
sd <- sqrt(0.25)

set.seed(0858)
y <- datasimu.l1(J=J, cs=cs, beta=beta.mcie, sd=sd)
prop.table(colSums(y))
##     y1     y2     y3 
## 0.3368 0.5016 0.1616
uniDLL <- 'uniGLMM';invisible(TMB::compile(paste0(uniDLL, '.cpp')))
## dyn.load(TMB::dynlib(uniDLL))
checkDLL(uniDLL)
## Loading DLL
Z <- modelZ(J=J, cs=cs)
u <- numeric(J)

obj <- TMB::MakeADFun(data=list(Y=y, Z=Z),
                      parameters=list(beta1=0,
                                      beta2=0,
                                      logsd=log(0.1),
                                      u=u),
                      DLL=uniDLL, ## ----------------------------------
                      random='u', hessian=TRUE, silent=TRUE)
(opt <- with(obj,
             nlminb(par, fn, gr)))
## $par
##      beta1      beta2      logsd 
##  0.7942143  1.1925280 -0.8644417 
## 
## $objective
## [1] 2515.155
## 
## $convergence
## [1] 0
## 
## $iterations
## [1] 19
## 
## $evaluations
## function gradient 
##       29       20 
## 
## $message
## [1] "relative convergence (4)"
bind_cols(
    bind_rows(
        opt$par, c(beta.mcie, logsd=log(sd))
    ),
    label=c('model', 'data')
)
## # A tibble: 2 x 4
##   beta1 beta2  logsd label
##   <dbl> <dbl>  <dbl> <chr>
## 1 0.794  1.19 -0.864 model
## 2 0.85   1.25 -0.693 data
sdr <- sdreport(obj)
summary(sdr, select='fixed')
##         Estimate Std. Error
## beta1  0.7942143 0.07272324
## beta2  1.1925280 0.06998907
## logsd -0.8644417 0.24931449
summary(sdr, select='report')
##     Estimate Std. Error
## sd 0.4212867  0.1050329
summary(summary(sdr, select='random'))
##     Estimate           Std. Error    
##  Min.   :-0.483663   Min.   :0.3797  
##  1st Qu.:-0.066541   1st Qu.:0.3827  
##  Median : 0.077759   Median :0.3827  
##  Mean   :-0.009257   Mean   :0.3868  
##  3rd Qu.: 0.077759   3rd Qu.:0.3954  
##  Max.   : 0.224766   Max.   :0.4145
prof.beta1 <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='beta1', trace=FALSE)
prof.beta2 <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='beta2', trace=FALSE)
prof.logsd <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='logsd', trace=FALSE)

par(mfrow=c(1, 3))
plot(prof.beta1);abline(v=beta.mcie['beta1'], lty=2, col='red')
plot(prof.beta2);abline(v=beta.mcie['beta2'], lty=2, col='red')
plot(prof.logsd);abline(v=log(sd), lty=2, col='red')

uni2GLMM

INDEPENDENT RANDOM INTERCEPTS

TAKE-HOME MESSAGE: PARALLELIZATION + MULTIPLE PARAMETER_VECTOR() + MULTIPLE dnorm() + MODELING THE log(sd) WORKS NICELY!

sd <- c(sqrt(0.25), sqrt(0.15))

set.seed(0859)
y <- datasimu.l1(J=J, cs=cs, beta=beta.mcie, sd=sd)
prop.table(colSums(y))
##     y1     y2     y3 
## 0.3456 0.4932 0.1612
uni2DLL <- 'uni2GLMM';invisible(TMB::compile(paste0(uni2DLL, '.cpp')))
## dyn.load(TMB::dynlib(uni2DLL))
checkDLL(uni2DLL)
## Loading DLL
u1 <- u2 <- numeric(J)

obj <- TMB::MakeADFun(data=list(Y=y, Z=Z),
                      parameters=list(beta1=0,
                                      beta2=0,
                                      logsd1=log(0.1),
                                      logsd2=log(0.1),
                                      u1=u1,
                                      u2=u2),
                      DLL=uni2DLL, ## ----------------------------------
                      random=c('u1', 'u2'), hessian=TRUE, silent=TRUE)
(opt <- with(obj,
             nlminb(par, fn, gr)))
## $par
##      beta1      beta2     logsd1     logsd2 
##  0.7334667  1.1190578 -0.7817026 -0.9350711

## $iterations
## [1] 27
## 
## $evaluations
## function gradient 
##       37       28 
## 
## $message
## [1] "relative convergence (4)"
bind_cols(
    bind_rows(
        opt$par, c(beta.mcie, logsd1=log(sd[1]), logsd2=log(sd[2]))
    ),
    label=c('model', 'data')
)

summary(summary(sdr, select='random'))

prof.beta1 <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='beta1', trace=FALSE)
prof.beta2 <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='beta2', trace=FALSE)

prof.logsd2 <- TMB::tmbprofile(obj, name='logsd2', trace=FALSE)

par(mfrow=c(2, 2), mar=c(4, 4, 2, 2))
plot(prof.beta1);abline(v=beta.mcie['beta1'], lty=2, col='red')

uni6GLMM

CORRELATED RANDOM INTERCEPTS

COMPARING uni4GLMM WITH uni5GLMM, WORKING ON THE log(s2) TOOK LESS ITERATIONS. THUS, WE FOLLOW THAT

TAKE-HOME MESSAGE: PARALLELIZATION + PARAMETER_MATRIX() + MVNORM() + MODELING THE log(ss) WORKS! PROBABLY NEED MORE DATA TO BETTER ESTIMATE THE CORRELATION

cov12 <- -0.2*sqrt(0.25)*sqrt(0.15) ## -0.0387
sigma <- matrix(c(0.25, cov12, cov12, 0.15), nrow=2)
## chol(sigma) ## PD matrix

set.seed(0948)
y <- datasimu.l2(J=J, cs=cs, beta=beta.mcie, Sigma=sigma)
prop.table(colSums(y))
##    y1    y2    y3 
## 0.352 0.504 0.144
